observations.recommendation:
Management to require:
1) The CGSO to conduct Physical count of supplies and materials semestral and to prepare the corresponding RPCI;
2) The CGSO to consolidate the issuances of supplies and materials thru SSMI and submit the same together with the RIS to the CAO as JVs to the audit basis for recording the supplies and materials issued;
3) The CAO and CGSO to reconcile their records regularly; and
4) The CAO to make the necessary adjustments to reflect the correct balance of the inventory accounts in the financial statements.

We recommended that management:
a. Revise the conditions set forth in the Deed of Undertaking to ensure that grantees repay their loans whether or not the animals survived and to impose penalties or legal remedies for non-payment;
b. Require the City Agriculturist to regularly monitor and inspect the status of swine in the hands of loan grantees, to encourage grantees to repay their loans and to reconcile her records with the accounting records;
c. Require the City Accountant to recognize loan receivables for loans granted on the basis of the Deeds of Undertaking signed by the recipients.

We recommended that management improve the implementation of Solid Waste Management pursuant to R.A. 9003 through the following:
a) Adopt a viable and effective collection schedule for specific types of wastes to be collected;
b) Acquire additional garbage trucks to implement waste segregation at source and point of collection;
c) Widen the coverage of the city’s garbage collection system; and
d) Require the SWM Board to strengthen their Information, Education and Communication (IEC) Program to increase the awareness of the constituents on waste management.
